Description:
Convenience in The Grove!
Introducing an EAST facing block of land in The Grove Estate of Tarneit. This block is titled & ready for you to build your dream home. Perfect choice for both single and double storey homes.
The Grove Estate offers beautiful creek side living without sacrificing great access to education, retail amenities and recreational facilities.
Consider yourself lucky being conveniently positioned less than 500 metres to Davis Creek, Walking trail and Wooten Road Reserve (containing two football fields and nine tennis courts) and less than 600 metres to the proposed Town Centre and future state Primary and Secondary Schools. You will also be located just 5km to the newly refurbished Pacific Werribee Shopping Centre.
Please make your ONE call now.
ONE Agency Wyndham wishes you success in your search for a beautiful home.

Description:
Superb Low Maintenance Lifestyle
An inspiring celebration of upgraded quality, meticulous attention-to-detail, and a radiant range of free-flowing space, this simply stunning double-storey family residence showcases seamless indoor/outdoor perfection.
Fantastically designed with a functional floor plan incorporates the formal lounge/ downstairs 4th bedroom, spacious open-plan living/dining merges effortlessly with a well-equipped gourmet kitchen boasting stainless steel appliances, before extending outdoors to a private entertaining patio. The impressive layout continues upstairs with a versatile retreat and all three generously-sized bedrooms. The magnificent master boasts an enormous dual mirrored walk-in robes the remaining bedrooms include built-in robes while sharing a stunning 2-way bathroom which showcases the double vanity, separate shower and bath.
Superior finishing touches include high ceilings, alarm, CCTV, floorboards, double remote garage, downlights, decking, curtains and blinds to all windows & patio doors. Plus cooling & ducted heating throughout for all year comfort.
Conveniently located within moments of excellent amenities including Ginifer Train Station, Sunshine Hospital, Victoria University, Cairnlea Town Centre, Brimbank Shopping Centre, parklands and minutes from the Western Ring Road/Western Highway, this home has loads of appeal and is sure to impress. Don't Miss Out!
***PHOTO IDENTIFICATION IS REQUIRED FOR ALL INSPECTIONS***

Description:
Comfortable Living, Entertainers Delight And A Granny Flat As A Bonus
3D Virtual Tour available for this property. To find out more about this property, please contact us on 03 9131 4000
Looking for a property that has it all? Look no further than this amazing property that offers both comfortable living and an enormous outdoor entertainment area, including a Granny Flat with much-much more to offer.
Situated in the popular Grange estate, within walking distance to Hogan's Corner Shopping Centre, Public and Private Schools, mainly Grange Primary P-12 College and St James Apostle. With just a short drive to the Pacific Werribee Shopping Centre, this property has all you would want in a home which includes upgraded comfortable living, an enormous outdoor entertainment area complete with built in woodfire pizza oven and spit roast. A corner lot with side access to backyard that can easily park two cars and a fully self-contained granny flat as a bonus.
Featuring:
- 4 Bedrooms with master having a full ensuite and walk in robes with built in cabinets
- Two bedrooms with built in robes
- Fully renovated kitchen
- Ample cupboard storage
- Quality stainless steel appliances including dishwasher
- Bench-top which compliments as a breakfast bar
- Two living areas giving you a separate lounge /theatre room
- Gas wall heater
- Spacious open living/meals area with an electric gas log fireplace
- Large laundry area with plenty of storage space and place for washing machine/dryer
- Enormous fully covered pergola area
- Built in wood fire pizza oven & spit roast, perfect for parties and family gatherings
- Granny flat at the back complete with bedroom, ensuite, built in robe, lounge, kitchen and wall mounted heater
- Double garage with internal access
- All this on a corner block with access for two extra car spaces
Don't miss out on this amazing opportunity to secure a home situated in a central location with easy access to public transport, short drive to both the Metro and V Line train stations, mainly Hoppers Crossing and Tarneit as well and approximately 25km to Melbourne's CBD.
A home that has it all and much-much more is not one to be MISSED!
Fletchers COVID-19 Update
Fletchers remains committed to conducting our services in a safe and responsible manner.
Due to stage 4 restrictions, physical inspections are not currently permitted.
We encourage you to contact the agent and register your interest to book a private appointment as soon as restrictions are eased.
Under the latest measures, any work related to contact settlements or end-of-lease scheduled to occur during this period, may be undertaken. This also includes final inspections.
If you are attending a final inspection, you must wear a face mask and adhere to strict social distancing measures of 1 person per 4 square metres. All visitors must confirm that they are not ill and have not been in contact with someone who has contracted COVID-19 in the last 14 days.
Please note that Fletchers agents have the right to refuse entry to any premises during a final inspection if any visitors are presenting with physical symptoms or are not wearing a face mask.
For more information, please visit: fletchers.net.au/response-to-covid-19

Description:
Spectacular Entertainer in Superb Location
LJ Hooker Point Cook presents 26 Kirkstone Road, Point Cook. Superbly positioned within walking distance of all major amenities, this modern and immaculately presented home offers exceptional convenience. Showcasing two living zones, three bedrooms, two bathrooms and a spectacular entertainers alfresco, this single-storey home beckons families, downsizers and investors. With shops, schools and recreational facilities at your front door, leave the car at home and enjoy a life of leisure.
- Encouraging endless entertaining, the well-considered floorplan delivers uncompromised functionality for family living, with both formal and informal living zones. French doors allow natural light to flood the open plan family and meals spaces and provides an effortless transition to the covered alfresco.
- Calling for get-togethers with family and friends, the covered pergola is an entertainers dream, the large timber deck screened for privacy and comfort, housing a fully equipped outdoor kitchen with built in barbeque and pizza oven.
- Returning indoors, the contemporary kitchen has been crafted with care, designed to meet the needs of any home chef. Expansive countertops include a central island, breakfast bar and coffee nook, bordered by an abundance of cabinetry, a full-sized pantry and stainless-steel appliances including a gas cooktop, under bench oven and dishwasher.
- Accommodation comprises three bedrooms, each with generous proportions, built-in robes and carpets underfoot. The peaceful master suite is located at the front of the home, fitted with his-and-hers walk-in-robes and an en suite, while the remaining bedrooms share access to the central bathroom with a tub and separate toilet.
- Offering low maintenance living with landscaped gardens, mature shrubs and a paved sitting area.
- Further highlights of this wonderful home include a double remote-control garage with internal access, a separate laundry with storage, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, tiled living zones, ceiling fans and downlights throughout.
This ultra-convenient location is within walking distance of major amenities including Sanctuary Lakes Shopping Centre, Jamieson Way Community Centre, Lumen Christi School and Carranballac P-9 College. A hive of activity, residents will enjoy easy access to the walking tracks of Jamieson Way Reserve, Cheetham Creek and the Sanctuary Lakes Golf Club, as well as the Waterstone Cafe and Alamanda Cafe and Bistro. In addition to the picturesque Sanctuary Lakes neighbourhood, residents will enjoy the first-class amenities of the Sanctuary Lakes Recreation Club with a gym, indoor swimming pool, spa and sauna.

Description:
Peaceful Living with Uninterrupted Urban Views!!
This spectacular double storey home built by Porter Davis, located in the well sought after Saltwater Estate is designed for a spacious and relaxed family living. Situated in one of the most pristine locations close to Saltwater Coast Crocodile Park and Wetlands, this astonishing home is contemporary with a free flowing floor plan at its best.
- Five bedrooms, three bathrooms and a remote controlled double garage with internal access.
- Master bedroom incorporates a spacious full ensuite including double vanities with stone bench top, extended shower and a spacious his & her walk in robe. It comes with an access to its private balcony for serene views.
- There is a bedroom downstairs with twin built in robe and a semi-ensuite which is ideal for your guests to stay over. One of the minor bedrooms incorporates a walk in robe as well.
- You will be impressed by its stylish and modern open plan kitchen with 900mm high quality stainless steel appliances; glass splashback, s/s dishwasher; Caesar stone bench top with plenty of work space and a walk in pantry.
-Main entrance welcomes you with a double door, wide hallway and a formal lounge overlooking the front yard and PLUS one bedroom downstairs for convenient life style.
- Multiple living areas over two levels; Downstairs large informal family adjacent to the kitchen and overlooking open outdoor area. Upper level living addresses a spacious theatre room and retreat placed to all bedrooms for the whole family to enjoy.
-A low maintenance backyard for all hassle free entertainment throughout the year.
- Extra features include remote control double garage with internal access, powder room upstairs, ducted heating, air con in the Master Bedroom, security alarm, high ceiling, 5KW solar panels ,plantation shutters, fully landscaped low-maintenance front yard, back yard and much more to explore.
The master planned Saltwater Coast Estate offers residents access to the lifestyle centre, with pool, tennis courts, function room and café just a short walk away. An abundance of neighbourhood amenities includes quality schools, such as St Mary of the Cross Catholic Primary School, Saltwater P-9 College and Point Cook South Senior School opening soon .Attractions include Point Cook Coastal Park and bay, Cheetham Wetlands and the expansive Point Cook Road sporting ovals. Public transportation options include a bus link to nearby Williams Landing train station, Aircraft & Laverton while a newly planned shopping precinct is currently being planned.
Proudly Presented To You By First National Lakra. We Put You First!
Note: Photo-id required at the inspection. Every precaution has been taken to establish accuracy of the above information but does not constitute any representation by the vendor or the agent. Please make your own enquiries related to the property. Theatre photo has virtual display, equipments are not included. Backyard photo has virtual grass for display purposes only.

$610,000

Ricky Wadhwa and Prestige Group are proud to present this beautiful 4 bedroom 24 SQ home that is designed to impress with its modern features & low maintenance style.
This is a great home located on a generous sized block of 512sqm with 16m frontage.
Moments from all the fun-packed, family-focused facilities that are celebrated hallmark of a Saltwater Coast lifestyle, this stunning entertainer showcases a variety of supersized living spaces. Best of all, you can walk to Saltwater Community Centre with free access to Saltwater Coast Lifestyle Centre's fully equipped gym, tennis courts and swimming pool.
Discover a relaxed and versatile formal lounge, spacious open-plan living/dining, and a sleek, stainless-steel kitchen with island bench. Step outside and entertain on a paved patio, all ready for the addition of outdoor settings - and family and friends.
Offering an indulgent, low-maintenance lifestyle, all robed bedrooms are generously sized with the main bedroom featuring a striking ensuite and walk-in robes, while the family bathroom offers a deluxe bath and a walk-in shower. Comprehensive features include ducted heating and cooling, a garden and yard for a growing family, separate laundry and WC, and a remote-controlled double garage boasting internal entry.
Investors will appreciate the value and first homebuyers can enter the market with certainty in a fast-growing, family-friendly community within Saltwater P-9 School Zone, so close to the wonderful wetlands and wildlife of Saltwater Coast Crocodile Park.
$10,000 FHOG applicable.

Description:
Designer Living in a Sought After Location
This beautiful residence will impress the most meticulous buyer. Superbly presented with a desirable street presence and in a peaceful and sought after location. The spacious interiors combined with contemporary finishes and a relaxed flow of living zones to create seamless indoor/outdoor living and a home of timeless appeal.
* Four bedrooms and two bathrooms. Main bedroom includes large walk in robe and en suite bathroom
* Light filled living areas comprise spacious dining area integrating a stunning modern kitchen with clean lines, stainless steel appliances, large stone island bench with breakfast bar and waterfall finish, modern glass splashback, stone benchtops, ample workspace and storage plus stylish butlers pantry, adjoining tranquil living room with outlook to the serene backyard

* Features include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, monitored security alarm, three car garage with internal plus rear roller door access, neutral colour scheme, quality fixtures and fittings including timber flooring, window furnishings, high ceilings, light fixtures and downlights, floor to ceiling tiling in bathroom, landscaped low maintenance front and rear yard with mature plantings and so much more
Conveniently positioned in a quiet location close to Sanctuary Lakes amenities club house, bus stop and dining, dedicated cycling and walking trails around the lake and the creek, this home is a must see and is the epitome of stylish Resort Living.

Developers, investors & Home Owners, Embrace this fabulous opportunity.
In a well-established neighbourhood, a short stroll to Sunshine Train Station and Glengala Road shopping strip, seize this incredible opportunity and make this classic family home yours.
A welcoming front porch guides you inside, where a large formal lounge room sits alongside a spacious kitchen/meals area. Offers three sizeable bedrooms all with built in robes that share a central bathroom with a separate toilet. A huge sun room and backyard offer plenty of space to get outdoors, relax and entertain with family and friends.
Set on a generous block measuring 604sqm approximately, the home is a candidate for further renovation/extension, whilst also providing subdivision potential or the perfect site to build a luxury new home (STCA). Highlights include air-conditioning, a gas heater, and a large lock-up garage.
In a location well-suited to families, it's moments from Sunshine Heights Primary, Sunshine Market Place, bus services, Kororoit Creek Trail, Sunshine Secondary and less than 15km from Melbourne CBD.

This North facing 400sqm(approx.) is in a highly sought out pocket of Elpis Estate in Truganina.

It is an address perfectly positioned for convenience and growth. A place where you will take pride in your community and where your neighbors will become your friends.

Description:
Superb Side Access Bring the Boat or Caravan!
LJ Hooker Point Cook presents 40 Oriole Drive, Werribee. Ready and waiting for first home buyers and savvy investors, this spacious single-storey home is the perfect project. The well-considered floorplan suits growing families, the large, flat block a blank canvas complete with side access and room to store the boat or caravan. Situated on a quiet street, this home is ideally located within walking distance of popular Pacific Werribee, Heathdale Christian College, parks and playgrounds.
- The home begins with a super-sized and supremely comfortable living room and flows through to the air-conditioned family and meals zone, each space filled with natural light.
- Neat and tidy, the kitchen offers excellent counter space, a breakfast bar and full-sized pantry alongside quality appliances including a gas cooktop, wall mounted oven and griller.
- Accommodation consists of three bedrooms, each with built-in robes and carpeted floor coverings, the master with air conditioning, a ceiling fan and a private ensuite. The central bathroom has been beautifully modernized and includes floor-to-ceiling tiling and a decadent spa bath.
- The 615m2 approx. block features an expansive covered alfresco which is the perfect place to entertain family and friends no matter the weather, while the lush grounds are complete with a white picket fence, mature trees and a garden shed.
- Further highlights of this fabulous home include a double lock up garage, additional carport and side access, ducted heating, split system air conditioning and roller shutters.
Enjoying a superb location, this property is within walking distance of Pacific Werribee and Heathdale Christian College, with Werribee Mercy Hospital and Hoppers Crossing station just a short drive away. Ideal for families, local schools include Bethany Catholic Primary School, Westgrove Primary School and both University of Melbourne and Victoria University Werribee Campuses. Nearby leisure precincts include the Rhinos Rugby Union Football Club, Heathdale Glen Orden Wetlands and the Riverbend Historical Park.

Description:
Contemporary Style and Cottage Charm
LJ Hooker Point Cook presents 4/13B Riverbend Crescent, Werribee. Radiating warmth and exuding joy, this single-storey home is a delightful combination of contemporary style and cottage charm. Comprising three bedrooms, two bathrooms, open plan living and double car accommodation, this property is nestled within the quiet Riverbend Estate, with the Werribee River and Riverbend Historical Park at its doorstep. Well-suited to first home buyers, downsizers and investors, this property is within walking distance of several schools and enjoys easy access to local shops and public transport.
- Beautifully bright, the open plan living and dining zones are splashed in sunshine, with large windows on every wall and sliding doors leading to the tranquil garden. Outside, an alfresco with retractable awning and purpose-built barbeque accompany timber decking and Crazy-pave paving, the perfect space to entertain family and friends.
- At the heart of the home, the immaculate kitchen is timelessly styled with stone countertops, white cabinetry and glossy feature tiles. Stainless-steel appliances include a 900mm upright gas cooker and dual dishwasher drawers, while a breakfast bar and split system heating and cooling add functionality and comfort. The living are boasts a cosy gas fireplace and there is also zoned central heating throughout the home.
- Three bedrooms include the palatial master suite, with a walk-in-robe, split system heating and cooling and private en suite with rainfall showerhead. The remaining bedrooms are fitted with built-in robes and share access to the stylish family bathroom, complete with a tub and separate toilet.
- Expertly designed by Keogh Builders, this immaculate 4-year-old home sits upon a 343m2 (approx.) low maintenance block with easy outdoor living spaces, including artificial turf, irrigation system, garden lighting and well-established gardens.
- Additional highlights include a double remote-control garage with internal access, a separate laundry, ducted heating, split system air conditioning, plantation shutters, Roman blinds and a garden shed.
Werribee offers everything residents could possibly need, including high street style shopping precincts and Pacific Werribee Shopping Centre. Local favourites including Werribee Open Range Zoo, Werribee Mansion & Werribee Park Golf Club are all within arms reach, as is easy access to the freeway and public transport facilities. Families will benefit from local schools and kindergartens including Westgrove Primary School, Wyndham Central College and Bethany Catholic Primary School, each within walking distance.
Note. All stated dimensions are approximate only. Particulars given are for general information only and do not constitute any representation on the part of the vendor or agent.

Description:
Spectacular Ex Display Home.
This magnificent North facing 36sq approximately Simonds ex display home is in the ever so popular Point Cook Gardens Estate and located on a highly sought after 600m2 approximately allotment. An opportunity to take advantage of, this quality built home is walking distance from Point Cook Town Centre, Emmanuel College, public transport and within a short stroll from Williams Landing Station.
Entering the home, you are immediately welcomed by the generous high ceilings and porcelain tiles. To your left, you have a spacious study room and a generous sized master bedroom inclusive of a walk in robe & enuite with a double vanity and spa bath. The hallway extends to provide a glimpse of the formal dining with log fire heating and formal lounge room. Remaining three bedrooms offers built in robes & ceiling fans.
An expansive family and meals area adorned with quality finishes and warm with an abundance of natural sunlight all year round. The kitchen boasts stainless steel appliances, stone bench tops, dishwasher, water filter and purifier. Overlooking the exceptional family area & rumpus room and through to a beautifully landscaped backyard perfect for the Australian outdoor lifestyle and entertaining of guests.
Further quality additions to the home include; high ceilings, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, brick fence with electric gate, security cameras & alarm system, security window shutters, front security door, fabric drapes on windows, rainwater tank with pump + 3 taps, solar panels 1.2kW, ceiling fans throughout and a double remote garage.
Be quick to contact Ray on 0402 517 213 or Vikki on 0434 114 819 to secure this fantastic opportunity!
